strings.Value: "Where might Tartuk be now?"
"How is the war with the mites progressing?"
"How can I help you in your war?"
"We will speak later. Farewell!"
"Very well. I shall deal with the mite queen."
"I have helped enough. You must fight without me."
"There is someone in your dungeon I wish to discuss."
"I may need the relic to enter the hall, if Tartuk is already there."
"Queen Bdaah has been defeated. You have nothing more to fear."
"What need have you of this 'dumbhead', Chief? They're just taking up space in your dungeon."
"Serves them right. A kobold prison is the proper place for Tartuccio's servants."
"Release them, Chief. How does holding a 'dumbhead' prisoner serve you?"
[Attack] "I need our alliance no more!"
"I won't kill you, Chief. Take your servants and leave."
[Finish him] "Yes. Say your last goodbyes."
"Greetingsss, friendsss!"
"Eetingsss! Endsss!"
"We fight mitesss! Mitesss break bridge. We break wall. Now all quiet."
"Passsage cleared. We make big attack!"
"Make! Big! Tack!"
"Don't know. He leave. If find relic, enter sssacred hall. Mite not go thisss hall! We have mite relic," {n}says the chief proudly.{/n}
"I asssk help. My ssshaman Tartuk go passsage under Old Sssycamore. Fight mite! Sssearch relic! I afraid he can't do. Friend find ssshaman? Kobold attack then!"
"Kobold ssstrong, fierccce! Not afraid! But mite Queen ssstrong too." {n}The Chief looks annoyed.{/n} "You ssslay Queen, I give reward. Mitess run away. No kobold die. Sssuccesss!"
"Sssuc! Cesss!" {n}The crier brandishes his weapon bravely, but he is clearly shaken when the Queen is mentioned.{/n}
"Fearlesss! I like."
"Ssscared." {n}The Chief looks disappointed.{/n}
"Tartuk bring them. Thisss dumbhead shhhout sssilly thingsss. Call Tartuk Tartuchhhio. Can't talk good!"
"This dungeon does not depress me. It is as good as any place for contemplating the frailty of life."
"The little tongue-tied monster accuses me of not being able to speak. Ironic," {n}scoffs Jaethal, contemplating her nails.{/n}
"I always knew that honesty could get a bard behind bars! But I didn't think it would happen so quickly..."
"'Tis unworthy of a ruler, to stoop to insulting his prisoners! And we merely tried to open your eyes, Chief."
{n}The Chief thinks for a while, scratching the back of his head with a clawed finger.{/n} "Fine. I give mite relic. You touch it door and enter! Then return relic."
{n}The kobold crier is so impressed, he speaks even before Chief Sootscale can respond.{/n} "Feated! Evil mitey Queen! Glory! Glory!"
{n}The Chief thumps the crier on the head.{/n} "No ssspeak before Chhhief! Friend ssstrong, fierccce! Reccceive award!"
"Agree. Ussselesss creature. Releassse!"
"Yes. Ussselesss. Let them go!"
"You alssso ssspeak funny." {n}Chief Sootscale shakes his head helplessly.{/n}
"Deccceasssed... Deccceasssed is Chief and Sssootssscale tribe..."
{n}The Chief clambers onto his feet, shaking from his wounds.{/n} "I need no pity. Take mite relic. Paysss for my life!"
